=======================================
MATRIX-MULT-1
<p>
The diagram below depicts a matrix transformation \(T\text{.}\)  In the plane
  on the left is shown the vector \(\xvec\) in red;  the plane on the
  right shows the vector \(T(\xvec)\).  You may vary the vector
  \(\xvec\) by clicking in the head of the arrow.
</p>
<p>
  <div style="text-align:center">
    <canvas id="topleft" width="250" height="250" hspace=5>
      Your browser does not support HTML5 Canvas.
    </canvas>
    <canvas id="topright" width="250" height="250" hspace=5>
      Your browser does not support HTML5 Canvas.
    </canvas>
  </div>
</p>
=======================================

There is an interactive figure to explore a matrix transformation that
goes here.  More later.

=======================================
MATRIX-MULT-2
<p>
The diagram below demonstrates the effect of a matrix transformation
  on the plane.  You may modify the matrix \(A\) defining the matrix
  transformation \(T\) through the sliders at the top.  You may also move
  the red vector \({\mathbf x}\) on the left, by clicking in the head of the
  vector, and observe \(T({\mathbf x})\) on the right.
</p>

<p>
  <div style="text-align:center">
    <canvas id="bottomsliders" width="450" height="100">
      Your browser does not support HTML5 Canvas.
